00:32:20,100 --> 00:32:22,000
Help me! Hurry!

449
00:32:22,100 --> 00:32:24,300
- [ Fabric Tearing ]
- [ Groaning ]

450
00:32:24,400 --> 00:32:27,000
Hurry!

451
00:32:27,100 --> 00:32:29,400
- I'm here.
- [ Shouts ]

452
00:32:29,500 --> 00:32:32,200
- Sit up.
- Help me. Reach. Reach! Reach! Reach!

453
00:32:32,300 --> 00:32:35,100
- Give me your hand.
- Hurry up. [ Groans ]

454
00:32:35,200 --> 00:32:37,500
- [ Groaning Continues ]
- Give me your hand.

455
00:32:37,600 --> 00:32:39,700
What are you trying to do,
kill me?

456
00:32:39,800 --> 00:32:42,300
- Shut up and give me your goddamn hand!
- Damn! Oh, my God!

457
00:32:42,400 --> 00:32:44,600
[ Shouting ]

458
00:32:44,700 --> 00:32:47,700
<i>Help me.! Please.!</i>

459
00:32:47,800 --> 00:32:50,800
Hold on, man.

460
00:32:51,000 --> 00:32:53,400
- Hurry!
- [ Grunting ]

461
00:32:53,500 --> 00:32:57,900
Oh, God! You-- You think we were up your
ass before? I'm gonna own you now, slick.

462
00:32:58,000 --> 00:33:01,400
- What'd you say?
-Just pull me up!

463
00:33:01,500 --> 00:33:02,800
Pull me up.

464
00:33:03,900 --> 00:33:06,800
[ Groans ]
Come on. Pull me up. Hurry!

465
00:33:06,900 --> 00:33:11,600
[ Groaning ]
Pull me up! Now! Now!

466
00:33:11,800 --> 00:33:15,400
[ Screaming ]

467
00:33:15,500 --> 00:33:17,400
<i>[ Thud ]</i>

468
00:34:01,900 --> 00:34:04,900
I'm startin' to feel much more
in control of my anger.

469
00:34:05,000 --> 00:34:07,900
Well, that's quite a leap in progress.

470
00:34:08,000 --> 00:34:10,200
<i>Especially considering your recent tragedy.</i>

471
00:34:10,300 --> 00:34:12,200
Yeah.

472
00:34:12,300 --> 00:34:15,800
Well, I can't let the fact that
four paparazzis nearly killed my family...

473
00:34:15,900 --> 00:34:17,800
affect my behavior, now, can I?

474
00:34:17,900 --> 00:34:19,800
<i>What do you mean by that, Bo?</i>

475
00:34:19,900 --> 00:34:23,800
Well, you asked me to work
on something, and, uh, I did.

476
00:34:23,900 --> 00:34:27,000
Well, surely you must have
some feelings about what happened.

477
00:34:27,200 --> 00:34:29,600
I feel cheated.

478
00:34:31,000 --> 00:34:32,900
I'm angry.

479
00:34:36,100 --> 00:34:38,300
Blessed.

480
00:34:38,400 --> 00:34:40,400
All at the same time.

481
00:34:42,700 --> 00:34:44,600
- [ Sighs ]
- <i>What's this?</i>

482
00:34:44,700 --> 00:34:46,600
Ajournal.

483
00:34:46,700 --> 00:34:50,600
I want you to start recording specific events
that prompt your anger...

484
00:34:50,700 --> 00:34:52,800
<i>and how you dealt with them</i>
<i>in the moment.</i>

485
00:34:52,900 --> 00:34:55,400
Doing this will help you
put a face on your problems.

486
00:34:55,500 --> 00:34:58,800
My problems already
have faces, Dr. Kelley.

487
00:34:58,900 --> 00:35:01,200
Well, then you're moving
in the right direction.

488
00:35:03,200 --> 00:35:06,100
Let this journal become
a sanctuary for you, Bo.

489
00:35:06,200 --> 00:35:08,500
My clients are having
great success with it.

490
00:35:08,600 --> 00:35:10,800
Really?

491
00:35:20,300 --> 00:35:22,200
<i>[ Elevator Dings ]</i>

492
00:35:33,200 --> 00:35:35,000
This shit happens way too often.

493
00:35:35,100 --> 00:35:37,500
This kid never even hit the brakes.

494
00:35:37,600 --> 00:35:40,800
- This guy ain't no kid. He's close to 40.
- They call 'em Rolex riders.

495
00:35:40,900 --> 00:35:43,800
They hang out in Beverly Hills,
wear expensive leathers.

496
00:35:43,900 --> 00:35:46,200
Same guy cuts all their hair.
Pity. He was cute.

497
00:35:46,300 --> 00:35:49,700
Hey, fellas.
Detective Burton, S.I.S.

498
00:35:49,800 --> 00:35:52,700
- You boys mind if I sniff around?
- Knock yourself out, Detective.

499
00:35:52,800 --> 00:35:54,700
Hey, why's Special Investigations...

500
00:35:54,800 --> 00:35:57,200
sending a D-2 down
to a traffic accident?

501
00:35:57,300 --> 00:35:59,700
Well, I heard your victim's name
on the radio.

502
00:35:59,800 --> 00:36:02,200
He was part of a case
that I've been working on.

503
00:36:02,300 --> 00:36:04,900
It's probably nothing.
I just thought I'd look around.

504
00:36:18,100 --> 00:36:20,000
<i>Here you go, sweetie.</i>

505
00:36:20,100 --> 00:36:22,200
- Thank you.
- Sure.

506
00:36:24,200 --> 00:36:26,600
- Anything else?
- Mm-mmm.

507
00:36:26,700 --> 00:36:28,300
I'm fine.

508
00:36:28,400 --> 00:36:31,100
- Okay.
