00:38:28,600 --> 00:38:30,600
Chrissy!
Hey, baby.

532
00:38:38,400 --> 00:38:40,900
<i>Hey. What do you got?</i>

533
00:38:41,000 --> 00:38:43,300
Just like I expected. Cops refused
to release Kevin's personal effects.

534
00:38:43,400 --> 00:38:46,600
- Then what are we doin'--
- Would you let me finish? I said I expected it.

535
00:38:46,700 --> 00:38:50,100
So I slapped 'em with a bogus power
of attorney. They didn't have any choice.

536
00:38:50,200 --> 00:38:52,800
Ready for the good news?

537
00:38:52,900 --> 00:38:55,400
Cheryl.
Do you mind, love?

538
00:39:00,100 --> 00:39:02,200
Check this out.

539
00:39:03,700 --> 00:39:06,100
<i>[ Man ]</i>
<i>Kevin.!</i>

540
00:39:06,200 --> 00:39:08,600
Even in death,
they can't shut him up.

541
00:39:08,700 --> 00:39:12,200
Hey, Cheryl. Call Richard.
Tell him to hold the cover.

542
00:39:15,700 --> 00:39:19,000
<i>[ Cheryl ] Hello, Debra.</i>
<i>Can you get me through to Richard?</i>

543
00:39:19,100 --> 00:39:22,000
<i>We got something here.</i>
<i>We need to speak with him now.</i>

544
00:39:26,300 --> 00:39:28,200
Bo?

545
00:39:28,300 --> 00:39:30,200
- Bo! Howdy.
- Hey, Detective.

546
00:39:30,300 --> 00:39:32,200
- How are you?
- Good. How you doin'?

547
00:39:32,300 --> 00:39:34,800
Okay. Good to see you.
Yeah, things are good.

548
00:39:34,900 --> 00:39:37,800
- You want a cup of coffee?
- <i>I'd love one. Thanks.</i>

549
00:39:37,900 --> 00:39:41,000
- Let's take a walk. I'll show you around.
- Okay.

550
00:39:41,100 --> 00:39:45,000
Listen, the other day after I hung up with you
I did some digging around.

551
00:39:45,100 --> 00:39:48,200
We're dealing with
real scumbags here, Bo.

552
00:39:48,300 --> 00:39:49,900
This guy-- Leonard Clark?

553
00:39:50,000 --> 00:39:52,400
He used to be an attorney.

554
00:39:52,500 --> 00:39:55,600
He got himself disbarred
for distribution of narcotics.

555
00:39:55,700 --> 00:39:56,700
Is that right?

556
00:39:56,800 --> 00:39:59,700
What do you think
the son of a bitch does?

557
00:39:59,800 --> 00:40:02,800
He turns around and sues the police
department for illegal search and seizure.

558
00:40:02,900 --> 00:40:05,600
Cost the city a million bucks
just to make it go away.

559
00:40:05,700 --> 00:40:08,700
He's still on probation for
possession of illegal firearms.

560
00:40:08,800 --> 00:40:10,000
Really.

561
00:40:10,100 --> 00:40:14,200
And this other guy-- Harper?
The guy you slapped around?

562
00:40:14,300 --> 00:40:16,900
He slimed his way out of
an attempted rape charge.

563
00:40:17,000 --> 00:40:18,800
Guess who the attorney was.

564
00:40:18,900 --> 00:40:20,800
- Leonard Clark?
- Yeah.

565
00:40:20,900 --> 00:40:23,800
And by the way, you're not
the first deep pockets he got into.

566
00:40:23,900 --> 00:40:26,400
- This actor, Andy Baldwin?
- Alec?

567
00:40:26,500 --> 00:40:28,400
Yeah. One of
those Baldwin guys.

568
00:40:28,500 --> 00:40:30,400
Anyway, he slaps Harper around.

569
00:40:30,500 --> 00:40:32,400
Harper takes him to the cleaners...

570
00:40:32,500 --> 00:40:35,300
and then Harper moves into
a boat in the marina.

571
00:40:36,400 --> 00:40:38,300
Now, listen, Bo...

572
00:40:38,400 --> 00:40:41,300
until I get this thing straightened out--

573
00:40:41,400 --> 00:40:45,300
I know that you actors have people
and places you wanna keep confidential.

574
00:40:45,400 --> 00:40:47,300
Right.

575
00:40:47,400 --> 00:40:51,200
If I were you, I would be very careful
about what I said on my cell phone.

576
00:40:51,300 --> 00:40:54,100
- Really. Why's that?
- Because for a couple hundred dollars...

577
00:40:54,200 --> 00:40:57,000
you can go to
your local radio guy...

578
00:40:57,100 --> 00:40:59,400
and you can drop in
on anybody at any time.

579
00:40:59,500 --> 00:41:02,300
- <i>Bo, we're ready for you on set.</i>
- Okay.

580
00:41:02,400 --> 00:41:05,300
Listen, Detective, thanks for coming by.
I appreciate it.

581
00:41:05,400 --> 00:41:07,800
I'll speak to you soon.
Okay? Thank you.

582
00:41:08,000 --> 00:41:10,100
Thank <i>you.</i>

583
00:41:19,500 --> 00:41:21,900
I'm scared for Zach. I--

584
00:41:22,000 --> 00:41:26,400
Part of me just wants to take him
back to Montana where he can feel secure.

585
00:41:26,500 --> 00:41:28,900
<i>I don't think</i>
<i>he's gonna get that here.</i>

586
00:42:08,800 --> 00:42:10,900
[ Engine Starts ]

587
00:42:35,300 --> 00:42:37,500
[ Beeping ]

588
00:42:45,100 --> 00:42:47,300
[ Beeping Continues ]

589
00:42:57,500 --> 00:43:00,400
[ Beep Dialing ]

590
00:43:00,500 --> 00:43:02,400
[ Line Rings ]

591
00:43:02,500 --> 00:43:05,500
[ Scanner: Static,
Cell Phone Line Ringing ]

592
00:43:07,000 --> 00:43:10,600
- Hey, Reg. Where you at, man?
- Yeah, I just got here.

593
00:43:10,700 --> 00:43:13,000
[ Bo ] Nicole Kidman's
coming by for a lunch meeting.

594
00:43:13,100 --> 00:43:15,000
- [ Reggie ] I'm on it.
- See you in a sec.

595
00:43:15,100 --> 00:43:17,000
<i>[ Beeps ]</i>

596
00:43:17,100 --> 00:43:19,000
[ Exhales ]

597
00:43:19,100 --> 00:43:22,100
You hear that, Leonard,
you piece of shit?

598
00:44:09,300 --> 00:44:11,400
Sorry, man.
Can't let you slide.

599
00:44:11,500 --> 00:44:13,900
- Mr. Laramie's orders.
- [ Chuckles ]

600
00:44:14,000 --> 00:44:16,100
- Do you mind?
- Yes, I do.

601
00:44:16,200 --> 00:44:18,400
- <i>What's going on, Reg?</i>
- Uninvited guest.

602
00:44:18,500 --> 00:44:20,400
Oh, yeah?

603
00:44:20,500 --> 00:44:23,400
I don't see anybody hurt or naked.
You sure you're in the right place, Leonard?

604
00:44:23,500 --> 00:44:25,400
Very funny.
Ha-ha-ha-ha.

605
00:44:28,400 --> 00:44:30,300
Get rid of him, Reg.

606
00:44:30,400 --> 00:44:33,100
- <i>You heard him.</i>
- Don't touch me!

607
00:44:33,200 --> 00:44:35,200
I'm leaving.

608
00:45:07,900 --> 00:45:11,100
[ Beep, Line Ringing ]

609
00:45:11,200 --> 00:45:13,100
[ Woman ]
Emergency Response.

610
00:45:13,200 --> 00:45:15,700
Listen, there's a guy with
a blue metallic Volvo station wagon--

611
00:45:15,800 --> 00:45:17,800
He's waving a gun
all over the place!

612
00:45:17,900 --> 00:45:19,800
- What is your location?
- Westbound on Sunset Boulevard!

613
00:45:19,900 --> 00:45:21,300
We're coming up to Western now!

614
00:45:21,400 --> 00:45:25,200
His license number is ABM543.

615
00:45:25,300 --> 00:45:28,700
He's a white guy! He's crazy!
Get somebody down here!

616
00:45:28,800 --> 00:45:30,800
<i>[ Line Disconnects ]</i>

617
00:45:33,300 --> 00:45:36,100
<i>[ Police Dispatcher ] All units, be on</i>
<i>the lookout for a blue Volvo wagon...</i>

618
00:45:36,200 --> 00:45:38,200
<i>license Adam-Baker-Mary 543.</i>

619
00:45:38,400 --> 00:45:40,300
<i>Approach with caution.</i>

620
00:45:40,400 --> 00:45:42,700
<i>Driver has priors</i>
<i>for illegal weapons possession.</i>

621
00:45:42,800 --> 00:45:45,600
<i>Last seen heading westbound</i>
<i>on Sunset near Western.</i>

622
00:45:58,300 --> 00:46:01,500
- [ Siren Blaring: Short Bursts ]
- [ Officer On Loudspeaker] Pull over immediately!

623
00:46:01,600 --> 00:46:03,500
- <i>Pull your vehicle over.!</i>
- Oh, bollocks.

624
00:46:17,900 --> 00:46:21,000
- Do you wanna see a license?
- <i>Show me your hands.! Get your hands up.!</i>

625
00:46:21,100 --> 00:46:23,200
- <i>Do it now.! Right now.!</i>
- What the hell is this?

626
00:46:23,300 --> 00:46:25,100
<i>[ Officer ]</i>
<i>Gun.!</i>

627
00:46:58,900 --> 00:47:02,400
And I'll let you stay up
as late as you want...

628
00:47:02,500 --> 00:47:04,400
until 1 0:00.

629
00:47:09,600 --> 00:47:12,200
Do you want a new bike?

630
00:47:16,700 --> 00:47:18,600
We need you to wake up.

631
00:47:19,800 --> 00:47:21,800
[ Sighs ]

632
00:47:24,100 --> 00:47:24,400
<i>One man is dead in what people are</i>
<i>describing as a bizarre "suicide by cop. '"</i>

633
00:47:24,400 --> 00:47:28,400
<i>One man is dead in what people are</i>
<i>describing as a bizarre "suicide by cop. '"</i>

634
00:47:28,500 --> 00:47:31,300
<i>The victim, Leonard Clark,</i>
<i>pointed a weapon at several officers...</i>

635
00:47:31,400 --> 00:47:33,300
<i>who were forced to open fire...</i>

636
00:47:33,400 --> 00:47:35,300
killing the man instantly.

637
00:47:35,400 --> 00:47:38,800
Details are still sketchy,
but police are describing the weapon...

638
00:47:38,900 --> 00:47:41,300
<i>as a modified.45-caliber blank gun...</i>

639
00:47:41,400 --> 00:47:43,800
<i>commonly used</i>
<i>in the motion picture industry.</i>

640
00:47:43,900 --> 00:47:46,300
<i>We're awaiting a press conference</i>
<i>by the authorities...</i>

641
00:47:46,400 --> 00:47:49,000
<i>and we'll bring it to you live,</i>
<i>when it happens.</i>

642
00:47:51,700 --> 00:47:54,600
<i>[ Phone Rings ]</i>

643
00:47:55,700 --> 00:47:57,700
<i>[ Ringing Continues ]</i>

644
00:47:57,800 --> 00:48:00,200
<i>[ Man On Machine ] Hi. You've reached</i>
<i>Wendell Stokes Photography.</i>

645
00:48:00,300 --> 00:48:02,900
<i>You got somethin'to say, say it.</i>

646
00:48:03,000 --> 00:48:05,400
- <i>[ Beep ]</i>
- <i>Wendell, it's Rex. Pick up the phone.!</i>

647
00:48:05,500 --> 00:48:08,400
<i>Leonard's dead.!</i>
<i>Pick up the phone.!</i>

648
00:48:16,500 --> 00:48:19,400
- It was Laramie, and I know it.
- Did you call Burton?

649
00:48:19,500 --> 00:48:22,900
Yeah. Know what he said?
""The case is under investigation.''

650
00:48:23,100 --> 00:48:26,000
Look, he's coming for us next, man.
You know that.

651
00:48:26,100 --> 00:48:29,300
Yeah, but at least
we'll know <i>when</i> he's coming.

652
00:48:29,400 --> 00:48:31,800
The cops don't
go after him, Wendell...

653
00:48:34,100 --> 00:48:36,000
we will.

654
00:48:36,100 --> 00:48:38,500
- <i>Did you get those from Rudy?</i>
- Yep.

655
00:48:38,600 --> 00:48:41,500
Oh, these are beauties.

656
00:48:41,600 --> 00:48:44,000
They'll transmit
to my system perfectly.

657
00:48:44,100 --> 00:48:46,500
H-How are we supposed to get in?

658
00:48:46,600 --> 00:48:48,700
Have a little faith, my friend.

659
00:48:48,800 --> 00:48:52,900
Now, you would think
people would be more careful.

660
00:49:00,700 --> 00:49:03,100
- <i>[ Bo ] Are you gonna be all right?</i>
- <i>[ Abby ] Mm-hmm.</i>

661
00:49:03,200 --> 00:49:05,600
If I don't feel well,
I'll have Ken cover my class.

662
00:49:05,700 --> 00:49:09,400
Well,just call me and I'll have Reggie
pick you up if there's any problem.

663
00:49:09,500 --> 00:49:11,300
Shh! I'll be fine.

664
00:49:11,400 --> 00:49:13,700
- Okay. All right.
- [ Giggles ]

665
00:49:13,800 --> 00:49:15,900
I'll be with Zach all afternoon.

666
00:49:16,000 --> 00:49:19,200
- I'll see you two for lunch at the hospital.
- Mm-hmm.

667
00:49:21,500 --> 00:49:23,400
- I love you, beautiful.
- I love you too.

668
00:49:23,500 --> 00:49:26,100
- I'll see you soon.
- Okay.

669
00:49:38,600 --> 00:49:41,000
- How's Zach?
- He's still in stable condition.

670
00:49:41,100 --> 00:49:43,000
- Thanks for asking.
- That's good news, Bo.

671
00:49:43,100 --> 00:49:46,000
- What you got?
- It might be a while. We're running a little behind.

672
00:49:46,100 --> 00:49:49,000
I have script changes for you,
and there's a Detective Burton here.

673
00:49:49,100 --> 00:49:52,400
- I told him he could wait in your trailer.
- He's in my trailer? Thanks.

674
00:49:55,600 --> 00:49:57,100
- <i>Oh, hiya, Bo.</i>
